-- Warsaw Bourse IPO May Give 35% Stake to Retail Investors, Rp.pl Reports
-- B y   D a v i d   M c Q u a i d
-- 2010-10-12T05:21:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-12/warsaw-bourse-ipo-may-give-35-stake-to-retail-investors-rp-pl-reports.html
Poland’s Treasury Ministry is
considering offering retail investors up to 35 percent of the 64
percent stake in the Warsaw Stock Exchange it is selling in an
initial public offering, the newspaper Rzeczpospolita said on
its rp.pl website, citing people involved in the transaction.  Investment banks advising the ministry are recommending that
25 percent to 30 percent of the IPO shares be allocated to
retail investors, rp.pl said. Poland’s market regulator is to
approve the Warsaw Stock Exchange’s share prospectus today,
clearing the way for the bourse to start trading on Nov. 9,
according to the newspaper.  Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
